Getting ready to make something sweet and special for the France Retreat guests.  Plans and preparations are happening in a flurry both for our family adventures in Europe + the Retreat south of Paris.  Sweet times.  Sometimes I think this phase is as-good / better than the actual trip.  #frenchwillowgathering #willowgathering #thejeffordsgetaway

Painting on a gently slopping hill overgrown with wild French poppies, kids running around, making tiny worlds in the grass, husband laying on a blanket reading a book, picnic basket emptied... one of my dream-days for our month in Europe.  We leave in just a few weeks!  Much to do.  Much to dream of.

Cyanotypes are beautiful and lovely and all... but they are also easy enough to do with your kids!  There are sweet memories all over my home from hours in the sun with my two daughters.  I love these pieces even more because of that. // sign up today (last day) to receive a beautiful box of supplies + workshop instructions at your door from @thecraftersbox.  Xox

Today is the last day to sign up for the cyanotype workshop and supply box from @thecraftersbox & I am taking over their Instagram feed today. 🙌🏽 Cyanotypes are SUCH a perfect art form for the warmer months - relaxing and refreshing to the max.  Sign up on their website and tell them I sent you!

This photo is deceptively quiet because my house is currently completely full of beautiful humans who are all standing/lounging just out of the frame for a second -- my family is enormous and I love them all.  It's so nice to have a space for all of us to gather and mess around in (even if I don't have enough dining room chairs yet.) Happy weekend everyone.
